 data-rtb=3D"true" data-wait-for-third-party=3D"false" data-targeting=3D"{}=
"></div>
</div></div></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_10-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html=
"> Plenty of other people, however, like to measure in amounts because that=
=E2=80=99s what they are familiar with or they don=E2=80=99t own a kitchen =
scale. This is where understanding the conversion of grams to cups is helpf=
ul. The conversion is different depending on whether the ingredient is liqu=
id or solid. But so long as you have a few measuring cups and measuring spo=
ons on hand, along with a conversion chart or access to an online calculato=
r, you are good to go about <a href=3D"https://www.southernliving.com/vanil=
la-cupcakes-8599707" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" dat=
a-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">your baking</a>.
</p>
